            moved Amendment No. 74:
            <q>Page 44, line 9, at end insert&#x2014;</q>
            <q>( ) A substitute bus service for a discontinued railway passenger service shall be guaranteed by the relevant national authority for a period of at least five years from the date of the discontinuation of the railway service, and such a guarantee shall include a frequency of service not less than that previously provided by the railway service.</q></p><p>
            <q>( ) The timetable of a substitute bus service for a discontinued railway passenger service shall be&#x2014;
            <ol>
            <li>(a) published in the national rail timetable; and</li>
